# Cursor Rules for this repository

## Language
- Always respond in Japanese.

## UI Libraries
- Prefer Tailwind CSS, shadcn, Magic UI, Lucide icons.
- Ask for approval before adding other UI libs.
- shadcn usage: `npx shadcn@latest xxx` or `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest xxx`.
- Magic UI: `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add "https://magicui.design/r/xxx"`.
- Lucide: `pnpm install lucide-react`.
- Avoid gradient colors.

## Fonts
- English: Hanken Grotesk Bold/ExtraBold.
- Japanese: Noto Sans JP.

## Error Handling Docs
- When an error occurs and is solved, document in `ERROR_SOLUTIONS/ERROR_SOLUTIONS_UNIFIED.md`:
  - Cause
  - Exact solution
  - Preventive measures
- If the same error happens twice or more, search the web or check `ERROR_SOLUTIONS.md`.

## Build & Deployment
- Run `npm run build` regularly and before pushing/Deploying.

## Documentation
- Update Design Document on feature add/update/removal (file TBD).
- Maintain `PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md` to clarify where to modify.
- Use naming convention to avoid UI lib conflicts: `{abbr}{Component}` e.g., `ShadTab`, `MagicDock`.
- Maintain `Lessons.md` for non-engineers; use analogies and concrete examples.

## Process
- Every three interactions, confirm with: "Cursor Rules確認完了 ✅".
- If any required document is missing, create it.
- Remind to check Cursor Rules every conversation.
- When `.cursorrules` is checked, say: `.cursorrules 読んだぞ！✨`.


